:INFO
Mushroom Grow Tent Troubleshooting
Common problems in mushroom grow tents and practical solutions. Most issues are caused by humidity, airflow, or contamination management.

:TASK
[ ] Pins not forming: Check humidity above 90 percent and increase FAE
[ ] Green mold on block: Remove immediately and sterilize the area
[ ] Mushrooms drying and aborting: Humidity too low or airflow too high
[ ] Leggy or pale mushrooms: Increase indirect light to 12 hours
[ ] Slow colonization: Raise temperature to 22 to 24 degrees Celsius
[ ] Water pooling on tent floor: Add drainage tray and reduce misting
[ ] Bacterial blotch on caps: Reduce direct misting onto fruiting bodies

:NOTE
Most contamination problems start outside the tent during inoculation. If contamination recurs after fixing in-tent conditions, review your inoculation workspace and sterilization process.